Encapsulation in Java (Simple Example)

Encapsulation = Hiding data using private variables and accessing them using getter and setter methods.



class func {

    String name;

    public String getname() {
        return name;
    }

    public void setname(String nam) {
        name = nam;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        func s = new func();

        s.setname("jayasri");

        System.out.println(s.getname());
    }
}



jayasri







Abstraction in Java (Simple Example)

Abstraction = Hiding implementation details and showing only the essential functionality.


Abstraction → Hides implementation (how something works).



abstract class Vehicle {

    abstract void run();
}

class Car extends Vehicle {

    void run() {
        System.out.println("Car needs a key");
    }
}

class Bike extends Car {

    void run() {
        System.out.println("Bike needs fuel");
    }
}

public class Main {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Bike b = new Bike();
        b.run();
    }
}


Bike needs fuel



